This paper is likely to belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category as it focuses on the use of distributed clusters for Machine Learning applications. It is also likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it discusses the use of Parameter Server (PS) paradigm for ML. Additionally, it may belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category as it discusses the theoretical guarantees and empirical behavior of iterative-convergent ML algorithms. It may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category as it discusses the implementation of a new PS system. Finally, it may belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category as it discusses the use of ML algorithms.
